For people who are having this problem, is it with really old save files? (By which I mean from before funds were implemented in 0.24)

That can cause issues. You need the vessel recovery SCENARIO{} in your save file. You can copy it from a fresh save if you know what you're doing.

Otherwise I don't know what to suggest unless you upload a log file somewhere and get someone knowledgeable to look at it, although there is the old remove mods until it works technique.

A little more than a month old now, of course.  Still relevant though.

I've been having the same issue with KSP 1.1.2 (x64) and 27 mods.  KW was one of those 27 mods and I was getting all sorts of instability; KSP crashed in space, in the VAB and upon recovery.  The recovery crash was quite common.  I came across this thread looking at the vessel recovery angle of my problem and saw DeathTBO's post.  I pulled KW from my mod set and relaunched.  Praise Jeb!  My KSP settled down and is now alot more stable.

Removing KW may not help everyone but it certainly helped me.
